  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The principal objective is to study clinical observations, symptoms and quality of life of
      non-small-cell lung cancer (NSCLC) patients undergoing specific non-operative treatment for
      cancer, including chemotherapy and radiotherapy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
